{"id": "EUVD-2024-53198", "enisaUuid": "0b11d649-0736-39f3-b085-1e963d1b581c", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ns390/stacktrace: Use break instead of return statement\n\narch_stack_walk_user_common() contains a return statement instead of a\nbreak statement in case store_ip() fails while trying to store a callchain\nentry of a user space process.\nThis may lead to a missing pagefault_enable() call.\n\nIf this happens any subsequent page fault of the process won't be resolved\nby the page fault handler and this in turn will lead to the process being\nkilled.\n\nUse a break instead of a return statement to fix this.", "datePublished": "2024-12-27T15:31:53", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-08T15:32:25", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/20c26357826457dc7c8145297e60ddc012e18914", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/588a9836a4ef7ec3bfcffda526dfa399637e6cfc", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-56550"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-56550"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0ec92ebc-6a81-3b8d-bca3-5dba7c4b2ff8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ebd912ff9919a10609511383d94942362234c077 <20c26357826457dc7c8145297e60ddc012e18914"}, {"id": "1813c475-bcbc-34dd-b038-a55d1875e731", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ebd912ff9919a10609511383d94942362234c077 <588a9836a4ef7ec3bfcffda526dfa399637e6cfc"}, {"id": "69e21d63-2784-3752-9827-4825f3f482c5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.4"}, {"id": "7d8c476b-4d42-3832-a549-08f3d21ca3a6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "c339d1d8-dacd-3521-9a65-051b9e76bc91", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13"}, {"id": "d54b7198-e480-3994-9fe3-7b191b5cb23e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.10"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "577645ce-0582-3c65-94aa-8a9cdb3428be", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": fals